article.headline: Southern Utah 63, Western Illinois 55
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- DeAngelo Newsom scored 20 points, grabbed six rebounds and had five steals to lead Southern Utah to a 63-55 victory over Western Illinois Thursday night. The Thunderbirds (9-15, 5-8 Mid-Continent Conference) led by as many as 21 points, before the Leathernecks (3-23, 1-13) narrowed it to 47-39 with just under five minutes remaining. The Thunderbirds widened the lead to 52-39 with a pull-up jump shot and a three-point play. Newsom was 8-for-9 from the floor and Tim Gainey added 13 points. T.J. Gray kept the Leathernecks in the game by hitting four 3-pointers in the final three minutes of the game, but it wasn't enough. Gray and Bobby Carter led Western Illinois with 14 points each. Southern Utah rushed out to a 16-1 lead as Western Illinois didn't score a field goal until 13:37 remained in the first half. The Thunderbirds shot 12-for-21 from the field before halftime and caused 12 Western Illinois turnovers. They led 30-13 at halftime.
